{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Aegis M2M Backend Test",
    "description": "Test collection for the aegis-backend-test service.\n\n## How to use\n\n**Step 1** — Run `1 · Login`. The backend authenticates itself to Aegis with its\n`clientId` and `clientSecret`. The token is saved automatically to `{{aegis_access_token}}`.\n\n**Step 2** — Run any request in `2` or `3` using that token as Bearer.\nThe backend validates the token against the Aegis public key (JWKS) and\ngrants or denies access to its own protected resources.\n\n**Step 3** — Run `4 · Negative Tests` to confirm the backend correctly\nrejects invalid or missing tokens.\n\n## JWT validation\n- **No roles** — only verifies the RS256 signature and expiry against `{{aegis_base_url}}/.well-known/jwks.json`.\n- **With roles** — same as above, plus checks that the required role is present in `roles[]`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1 · Login",
      "_postman_id": "f1000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "description": "The backend authenticates itself to Aegis using its clientId and clientSecret.\nThe returned Aegis-signed JWT is saved automatically to {{aegis_access_token}}.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (M2M)",
          "_postman_id": "f1000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/token",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["token"]
            },
            "description": "Calls Aegis:\n  POST {{aegis_base_url}}/api/v1/auth/{{aegis_country}}/token\n  Authorization: Basic base64(AEGIS_CLIENT_ID:AEGIS_CLIENT_SECRET)\n\nReturns the token and its decoded payload so you can inspect the claims (sub, roles, is_m2m, exp...).\nThe test script auto-saves access_token → {{aegis_access_token}}."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "try {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const token = json?.tokenResponse?.access_token;",
                  "    if (token) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('aegis_access_token', token);",
                  "        const p = json?.jwtPayload ?? {};",
                  "        console.log('Token saved. roles:', p.roles, '| is_m2m:', p.is_m2m, '| exp:', p.exp);",
                  "        pm.test('Token received', () => pm.expect(token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "        pm.test('is_aegis = true', () => pm.expect(p.is_aegis).to.be.true);",
                  "        pm.test('is_m2m = true', () => pm.expect(p.is_m2m).to.be.true);",
                  "    } else {",
                  "        pm.test('Token received', () => pm.expect.fail('access_token missing — check AEGIS_CLIENT_ID / AEGIS_CLIENT_SECRET in .env'));",
                  "    }",
                  "} catch (e) { console.error(e.message); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2 · Access resource — JWT (no roles)",
      "_postman_id": "f2000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "description": "The backend validates the Aegis JWT against the Aegis public key (JWKS).\nOnly the signature and expiry are checked — no role required.",
      "auth": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "bearer": [
          {
            "key": "token",
            "value": "{{aegis_access_token}}",
            "type": "string"
          }
        ]
      },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Public resource (no token needed)",
          "_postman_id": "f2000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/public",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "public"]
            },
            "description": "Open resource — no token required."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Protected resource (signature only)",
          "_postman_id": "f2000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/protected",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "protected"]
            },
            "description": "Token is verified against Aegis JWKS (RS256 signature + expiry).\nNo role is required — any valid Aegis JWT is accepted.\n\n→ 200  token valid\n→ 401  token missing, expired, or invalid signature"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Access granted', () => pm.expect(json.message).to.include('granted'));",
                  "pm.test('JWT claims returned', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.jwt).to.have.property('sub');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.jwt).to.have.property('roles');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.jwt.is_m2m).to.be.true;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3 · Access resource — JWT with roles",
      "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "description": "The backend validates the Aegis JWT AND checks that the required role is present in roles[].",
      "auth": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "bearer": [
          {
            "key": "token",
            "value": "{{aegis_access_token}}",
            "type": "string"
          }
        ]
      },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Admin resource (role: {{aegis_required_role}})",
          "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/admin",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "admin"]
            },
            "description": "Token verified (signature + expiry) AND roles[] must contain '{{aegis_required_role}}'.\n\n→ 200  token valid + role present\n→ 401  token invalid\n→ 403  token valid but role missing"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Access granted', () => pm.expect(json.message).to.include('granted'));",
                  "pm.test('Admin resources returned', () => pm.expect(json.adminResources).to.be.an('array').and.not.empty);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Role check — aegis-reader",
          "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/role/aegis-reader",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "role", "aegis-reader"]
            },
            "description": "Checks for role 'aegis-reader' in the token.\nReplace the last path segment with any role name to test it dynamically."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Role confirmed', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('aegis-reader'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Role check — ADMIN",
          "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000004",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/role/ADMIN",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "role", "ADMIN"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Role confirmed', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('ADMIN'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Role check — missing role (expect 403)",
          "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000005",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/role/non-existent-role",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "role", "non-existent-role"]
            },
            "description": "Token signature is valid but the role does not exist in roles[].\n→ 403 with required_role and token_roles listed."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 403', () => pm.response.to.have.status(403));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Forbidden error', () => pm.expect(json.error).to.include('Forbidden'));",
                  "pm.test('token_roles listed', () => pm.expect(json.token_roles).to.be.an('array'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4 · Negative Tests",
      "_postman_id": "f4000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "description": "Confirm the backend correctly rejects requests with no token, an invalid token, or the wrong role.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "No token → 401",
          "_postman_id": "f4000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/protected",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "protected"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
                  "pm.test('Error present', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().error).to.be.a('string'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Tampered token → 401",
          "_postman_id": "f4000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJmYWtlIn0.invalidsignature"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/protected",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "protected"]
            },
            "description": "Signature is invalid — the token was not signed by Aegis."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
                  "pm.test('JWT validation failed', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().error).to.include('JWT validation failed'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Valid token, wrong role → 403",
          "_postman_id": "f4000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000004",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{aegis_access_token}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/role/super-secret-role",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "role", "super-secret-role"]
            },
            "description": "Token signature is valid but 'super-secret-role' is not in roles[].\n→ 403 shows what roles the token actually has."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 403', () => pm.response.to.have.status(403));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('required_role in response', () => pm.expect(json.required_role).to.equal('super-secret-role'));",
                  "pm.test('token_roles listed', () => pm.expect(json.token_roles).to.be.an('array'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5 · Utils",
      "_postman_id": "f5000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health",
          "_postman_id": "f5000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Aegis JWKS (public key)",
          "_postman_id": "f5000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{aegis_base_url}}/.well-known/jwks.json",
              "host": ["{{aegis_base_url}}"],
              "path": [".well-known", "jwks.json"]
            },
            "description": "The public key the backend uses to verify all incoming Aegis JWTs."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
